Dajian Mountain, west of Nan'ao Island, is the highest peak in Shantou City in China's Guangdong Province. The lush mountain surrounded by clouds is home to more than 1,000 subtropical plant species. Wild tea trees hide in this forest. Check the video to see more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Guangdong Nan'ao Series Nan'ao Island in Guangdong Province is a rare habitat of greenery on the Tropic of Cancer. In June, the southeastern monsoon brings warm, moist air to the island, nurturing all lives: from ancient fig trees to newborn black-naped terns, from mysterious undersea creatures to medical herbs, which bestow Nan'ao Island with many stories. For more: Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 1: Windy Island Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 2: Reef Ninja Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 3: Brown-winged Dancer Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 4: Black-naped Tern Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 5: Living with Tides Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 6: Wind in the Sea Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 7: Bay Dwellers (Cover is a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)